                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d495">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.6211/197: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-20T18:00:00+03:00"
                            >September 20, 1939—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 20—3:06 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>578. I have learned from a reputable source that a German mission arrived in
                    Moscow today by air from Riga. As several German officers in uniform have been
                    seen in a Moscow hotel today the mission is apparently primarily one of a
                    military nature.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
